13:41.908 --> 13:48.697
♪

13:48.740 --> 13:51.569
[Engine purring]

14:04.365 --> 14:07.107
[Brakes squeal]

14:10.197 --> 14:11.285
[Speaking French]

14:15.158 --> 14:17.204
Sorry,
I-I don't speak French.

14:17.247 --> 14:19.597
-American?
-Since birth.

14:19.641 --> 14:24.124
I don't suppose you know
how to fix one of these?

14:24.167 --> 14:25.516
I was always under
the impression

14:25.560 --> 14:27.954
one just
threw them away.

14:27.997 --> 14:30.391
Well, hello there![Dog pants]

14:30.434 --> 14:32.219
Shall I take you and your
daughter back to the village?

14:32.262 --> 14:34.482
She's not my daughter,
and it'd be great

14:34.525 --> 14:36.745
if you could take us
anywhere but the village.

14:36.788 --> 14:38.703
I understand.
Please!

14:38.747 --> 14:40.140
Charlemagne can get
in the back.

14:40.183 --> 14:42.446
[Charlemagne yips]I wouldn't dare.

14:46.755 --> 14:49.410
[Charlemagne whimpering]

14:55.982 --> 14:58.288
First time
in a Rolls-Royce?

14:58.332 --> 15:00.900
First time in one
that smells like roses.

15:02.205 --> 15:04.294
I've been working
in the garden.

15:04.338 --> 15:05.730
I never had the feel.

15:05.774 --> 15:07.907
I find water
to be the key.

15:07.950 --> 15:11.345
Now you tell me.
[Chuckles]

15:12.346 --> 15:14.914
You speak
perfect English.

15:14.957 --> 15:17.220
I had a good teacher.

15:17.264 --> 15:18.830
Another talent I lack.

15:18.874 --> 15:21.746
Teaching?
Learning.

15:21.790 --> 15:23.748
You just have to be
taught by someone

15:23.792 --> 15:24.924
you want to listen to.

15:26.490 --> 15:29.537
I'm all ears.[Charlemagne pants]

15:33.062 --> 15:34.150
[Bells tolling]

15:34.194 --> 15:35.891
[Ethereal music playing]

15:35.935 --> 15:42.898
♪

15:42.942 --> 15:49.905
♪

15:49.949 --> 15:53.082
[Gentle music playing]

15:53.126 --> 15:58.479
♪

15:58.522 --> 16:05.921
♪

16:05.965 --> 16:14.016
♪

16:14.060 --> 16:20.414
♪

16:20.457 --> 16:23.330
[Speaks French]

16:23.373 --> 16:26.159
Madame Huchet.

16:29.814 --> 16:31.947
[Speaking French]

17:09.897 --> 17:11.421
What?

17:35.315 --> 17:37.447
Let's talk
in my office.

17:40.015 --> 17:41.495
[Door opens]

17:43.236 --> 17:45.020
See this here?

17:46.195 --> 17:48.676
You've got the early
stages of emphysema.

17:51.374 --> 17:52.506
Meaning?

17:54.508 --> 17:56.249
You have to quit smoking.

17:58.381 --> 18:00.470
Forget what you read,

18:00.514 --> 18:04.431
forget the TV commercials
with the sexy girls.

18:04.474 --> 18:07.695
Cigarettes are bad
for you.

18:07.738 --> 18:09.044
[Lighter clicks]

18:14.310 --> 18:16.007
Am I dying?

18:16.051 --> 18:18.488
No, but you're
killing yourself.

18:19.924 --> 18:21.839
How much time
do I have?

18:21.883 --> 18:23.711
Depends on you.

18:23.754 --> 18:25.887
Stop now, you'll live
another 30 years.

18:25.930 --> 18:29.064
Don't stop, you'll
live another 30 years,

18:29.108 --> 18:31.327
but you'll be
in an oxygen tent.

18:33.286 --> 18:35.375
Otherwise,
you're in great shape.

18:36.898 --> 18:38.378
Emphysema.

18:40.119 --> 18:42.338
Not pretty.

18:42.382 --> 18:43.774
[Indistinct conversations]

18:43.818 --> 18:45.080
[Soft music playing]

18:45.124 --> 18:48.083
♪

18:50.303 --> 18:57.571
♪

18:57.614 --> 19:05.013
♪

19:16.851 --> 19:19.114
[Dog barks]

19:22.465 --> 19:24.075
[Chicken squawks]

19:24.119 --> 19:25.642
[Children scream]

19:25.686 --> 19:29.124
-Bonjour.
-Bonjour!

19:31.866 --> 19:34.695
[Gravel crunches]

19:34.738 --> 19:41.092
♪

19:41.136 --> 19:44.270
[Children clamor]

19:49.884 --> 19:53.801
[Teacher speaks indistinctly
in French]

19:57.892 --> 19:59.589
[Gate bell ringing]

20:02.070 --> 20:03.854
[Children squeal and clamor]

20:03.898 --> 20:07.467
[Whistle blows]

20:17.041 --> 20:19.000
[Speaking French]

20:19.043 --> 20:21.611
[Speaking French]

20:27.226 --> 20:28.662
[Chuckles]

20:39.150 --> 20:41.501
[Lock and chain rattles]

20:53.382 --> 20:56.472
[Children clamor]

20:57.647 --> 20:59.780
[Speaks French]

21:10.878 --> 21:12.836
[Speaks French]

21:24.065 --> 21:26.676
Mr. Spade?

21:26.720 --> 21:30.158
How good to see you,
maestro.

21:30.201 --> 21:33.379
As always,
do sit down.

21:38.427 --> 21:39.907
Cigarette?

21:42.126 --> 21:43.737
You don't mind
if I have one?

21:43.780 --> 21:46.522
Not if you promise to blow
the smoke in my direction.

21:46.566 --> 21:48.698
[Laughs][Convent bell tolls]

21:52.006 --> 21:55.401
Your bells are a bit behind,
I have 10:24.

21:55.444 --> 21:58.099
For over 300 years,

21:58.142 --> 21:59.666
we sisters
climbed the tower

21:59.709 --> 22:01.885
and rang
the bells by hand.

22:01.929 --> 22:03.800
Then a salesman
arrives last month

22:03.844 --> 22:06.890
and convinces me to have
our bells automated.

22:06.934 --> 22:08.762
The mechanism
was installed last Friday.

22:08.805 --> 22:12.461
Since then, the bells now
ring whenever they choose.

22:12.505 --> 22:14.898
Maybe we're better off
not knowing exactly

22:14.942 --> 22:16.639
how much time we've got.

22:16.683 --> 22:19.686
Only if you aren't herding
children day until night.

22:19.729 --> 22:21.252
How are the children?

22:21.296 --> 22:25.387
Oh, thank the Lord,
very healthy and happy,

22:25.431 --> 22:29.913
though, some prefer
their solitude.

22:31.175 --> 22:33.787
There's plenty to be
said for solitude.

22:33.830 --> 22:36.442
God loves her
and keeps her safe.

22:38.139 --> 22:40.620
For his efforts
and yours.

22:42.491 --> 22:45.755
As always, we are very
grateful, Mr. Spade.

22:45.799 --> 22:47.409
A long time ago,
someone said to me

22:47.453 --> 22:50.804
that money and gratitude
don't always go hand in hand.

22:50.847 --> 22:53.763
A cynical someone,
no doubt.

22:53.807 --> 22:56.200
They were the only
"someones" I knew back then.

22:56.244 --> 22:57.985
Speaking of the past,

22:58.028 --> 23:01.249
her father is coming home
to Bazuel.

23:01.292 --> 23:03.120
You don't say.

23:03.164 --> 23:05.645
I assumed
that he was dead,

23:05.688 --> 23:07.603
but the dead
don't write letters.

23:07.647 --> 23:09.562
He has written several,

23:09.605 --> 23:11.346
all confirmed
by his mother

23:11.390 --> 23:13.392
to be in Philippe's
own hand.

23:13.435 --> 23:15.568
You've spoken
with Madame Saint-Andre?

23:15.611 --> 23:17.744
Audrey has become
very attentive

23:17.787 --> 23:19.093
to her granddaughter.

23:19.136 --> 23:21.922
Once a week,
she brings her clothing

23:21.965 --> 23:23.532
she has sewn herself.

23:23.576 --> 23:26.840
You didn't think this was
maybe something I should know?

23:30.844 --> 23:34.413
I'm telling you now
so that you are aware

23:34.456 --> 23:35.849
that he will be
here soon.

23:35.892 --> 23:38.329
Audrey could have written
those letters herself.

23:38.373 --> 23:39.418
To what purpose?

23:39.461 --> 23:40.680
The girl's rich.

23:40.723 --> 23:43.596
I assume
you mean spiritually.

23:43.639 --> 23:45.989
This isn't exactly
the Hotel Georges V.

23:46.033 --> 23:47.687
There's a trust fund
full of money

23:47.730 --> 23:49.993
that can only be described
as ill-gotten.

23:50.037 --> 23:53.344
Every dime goes to Teresa
when she turns 18,

23:53.388 --> 23:54.868
which I'm sure
Philippe knew,

23:54.911 --> 23:56.826
given his part in
separating said money

23:56.870 --> 23:59.220
from its rightful owners.

23:59.263 --> 24:02.223
Oh.

24:02.266 --> 24:04.878
Philippe Saint-Andre
is a thief?

24:04.921 --> 24:06.401
What a surprise.

24:06.445 --> 24:09.186
He stole the money with
the help of Teresa's mother,

24:09.230 --> 24:11.058
who apparently knew
Philippe well enough

24:11.101 --> 24:13.234
to put the money in
Teresa's name and not his.

24:13.277 --> 24:17.934
And you were involved
in this how, Mr. Spade?

24:17.978 --> 24:19.719
Peripherally.

24:19.762 --> 24:21.721
Philippe has always
denied paternity

24:21.764 --> 24:23.723
and until evidently,
very recently,

24:23.766 --> 24:25.289
his mother
has never acknowledged

24:25.333 --> 24:27.074
her granddaughter's
existence.

24:27.117 --> 24:30.251
But, now as Teresa
gets closer to 18,

24:30.294 --> 24:33.646
he's writing letters and
she's knitting pullovers?

24:33.689 --> 24:36.039
The war changed
a lot of people.

24:36.083 --> 24:37.476
Very few for the better.

24:37.519 --> 24:41.218
GrandmamanAudrey
is up to something.

24:41.262 --> 24:43.046
I always hoped that,

24:43.090 --> 24:45.527
with time,
Teresa would warm to you.

24:45.571 --> 24:47.660
I sent her mother
to rot in prison

24:47.703 --> 24:49.879
and her father
to die in Algeria.

24:49.923 --> 24:51.402
It's gonna be
a long wait.

24:51.446 --> 24:53.666
But she knows
that you care about her.

24:53.709 --> 24:56.233
Keeping a promise isn't
the same thing as caring.

24:56.277 --> 24:59.106
What I promised was
to bring the girl to Bazuel.

24:59.149 --> 25:02.326
Yes, well,
as the good book says,

25:02.370 --> 25:05.939
"He who promises
runs in debt."

25:05.982 --> 25:07.941
Is that Old Testament
or New?

25:09.116 --> 25:10.421
The Talmud.

25:10.465 --> 25:12.815
Aren't we full
of our own surprises?

25:12.859 --> 25:17.516
I do so enjoy our chats,
my dear Mr. Spade.

25:17.559 --> 25:19.126
[Soft music playing]

25:19.169 --> 25:26.481
♪

25:26.525 --> 25:28.875
[Gravel crunching]

25:28.918 --> 25:34.445
♪

25:34.489 --> 25:36.447
[Water trickling]

25:36.491 --> 25:38.841
What are you doing?
I fixed the dishwasher.

25:38.885 --> 25:41.148
[Speaking French]

25:49.243 --> 25:51.158
I'm on a health kick.

25:53.377 --> 25:55.597
So can I.

25:58.339 --> 26:00.297
Sorry,
I don't understand.

26:00.341 --> 26:01.951
Can you speak English?

26:15.922 --> 26:17.967
Do me a favor
and start locking the doors.

26:23.669 --> 26:27.194
Yeah, well, this trouble
needs no invitation.

26:30.327 --> 26:32.199
You don't seem
all that worried.

26:44.472 --> 26:48.215
[Mantel clock dings softly]

27:02.142 --> 27:06.015
[Mantel clock ticks]

27:06.059 --> 27:07.408
[Soft ethereal music playing]

27:11.020 --> 27:12.935
[Paper rustles]

27:12.979 --> 27:16.417
♪

27:16.460 --> 27:18.332
[Lighter cap clicking]

27:18.375 --> 27:25.252
♪

27:25.295 --> 27:32.172
♪

27:32.215 --> 27:34.348
[Clicking continues]

27:34.391 --> 27:42.269
♪

27:42.312 --> 27:50.103
♪

27:50.146 --> 27:59.112
♪

27:59.155 --> 28:02.681
[Child giggles]

28:02.724 --> 28:05.814
[Dog barking, child laughs]

28:05.858 --> 28:13.126
♪

28:13.169 --> 28:14.780
Gabrielle: How would
you like to earn a fee

28:14.823 --> 28:17.478
on top of what you're
already being paid?

28:17.521 --> 28:19.785
Sam:
Doing what exactly?

28:19.828 --> 28:21.961
What you're going
to do anyway,

28:22.004 --> 28:23.832
talk to
Philippe Saint-Andre.

28:23.876 --> 28:26.052
Just talk to him?

28:26.095 --> 28:27.880
He's blackmailing me.

28:27.923 --> 28:30.317
Over what?
You kill your husband?

28:32.667 --> 28:35.235
Okay.

28:35.278 --> 28:36.932
My husband was a Nazi.

28:36.976 --> 28:38.804
He was German?

28:38.847 --> 28:42.111
Worse, he was French.

28:42.155 --> 28:44.113
Jacques was
a collaborateur.

28:44.157 --> 28:47.943
And Philippe is threatening
to tell the authorities?

28:47.987 --> 28:49.336
Not only them,

28:49.379 --> 28:52.034
the newspapers,
the international press.

28:52.078 --> 28:53.470
Why would they care?

28:53.514 --> 28:55.037
I'm sure
a lot of partisans

28:55.081 --> 28:58.301
killed a lot of Nazi
collaborators back then.

28:58.345 --> 28:59.346
And their children.

28:59.389 --> 29:00.782
That was 10 years ago.

29:00.826 --> 29:02.088
What's different now?

29:03.524 --> 29:05.134
Algeria.

29:05.178 --> 29:07.658
Stopping Hitler was
something we could all agree

29:07.702 --> 29:10.487
was worth
whatever the cost.

29:10.531 --> 29:12.489
There is, however,
far less accord

29:12.533 --> 29:14.535
about our recent
conflict.

29:14.578 --> 29:16.276
And it certainly
doesn't help

29:16.319 --> 29:19.496
when both sides are locked
in some sick competition,

29:19.540 --> 29:22.021
committing one atrocity
after another.

29:25.764 --> 29:27.200
I grew up thinking

29:27.243 --> 29:30.551
that when my family went
on vacation to Laurent,

29:30.594 --> 29:32.335
we were going to
another part of France.

29:32.379 --> 29:34.381
And what do you
feel about it now?

29:35.991 --> 29:39.038
It only matters what
people think I feel.

29:39.081 --> 29:40.213
Just like
it doesn't matter

29:40.256 --> 29:41.780
that Jacques
had to be punished

29:41.823 --> 29:43.738
for betraying
the town of his birth,

29:43.782 --> 29:47.046
for aiding in the suffering
of his old friends,

29:47.089 --> 29:48.961
just so he could
sleep in his own bed,

29:49.004 --> 29:51.093
keep making his wine,

29:51.137 --> 29:53.487
or drive his
burgundy-colored car.

29:55.445 --> 29:57.491
But now, after this war,
if you're French,

29:57.534 --> 29:58.840
the only thing
that matters

29:58.884 --> 30:00.581
is that we punished
him ourselves.

30:00.624 --> 30:02.235
We?
Does that mean Philippe

30:02.278 --> 30:04.411
is blackmailing
more than just you?

30:04.454 --> 30:06.108
This is about me.

30:06.152 --> 30:09.329
I don't want the people
of Bazuel involved, please.

30:11.244 --> 30:12.636
I won't allow
the people here

30:12.680 --> 30:14.769
to live through such misery
all over again,

30:14.813 --> 30:16.292
which is
what will happen

30:16.336 --> 30:18.817
if Philippe carries
through on his threats.

30:18.860 --> 30:21.820
They're not afraid
of jail.

30:21.863 --> 30:24.866
They're afraid of being
remembered as war criminals,

30:24.910 --> 30:27.129
especially
by their children.

30:27.173 --> 30:28.870
I'd like to help you,

30:28.914 --> 30:31.046
but if I'm to get
my current fee,

30:31.090 --> 30:33.266
I gotta sort out
what to do with her.

30:35.355 --> 30:37.923
Man of conscience.
I understand.

30:37.966 --> 30:39.925
Man of many debts,
more like.

30:41.100 --> 30:42.231
To be honest with you,

30:42.275 --> 30:43.667
the sooner
I get her parked,

30:43.711 --> 30:46.018
the sooner
I can move on.

30:46.061 --> 30:47.584
I have a thought
on that,

30:47.628 --> 30:50.936
which will take
a few days to work out.

30:50.979 --> 30:53.590
Maybe I can pay you
to just think

30:53.634 --> 30:56.550
about how I can deal
with this situation

30:56.593 --> 30:58.552
without killing anyone.

30:58.595 --> 30:59.988
Oh, there's plenty
of ways

31:00.032 --> 31:02.077
of getting rid of a man
without killing him,

31:02.121 --> 31:03.949
especially when
there's a war on.

31:05.472 --> 31:07.300
Interesting.

31:07.343 --> 31:10.172
Your local constable
made it pretty clear,

31:10.216 --> 31:12.653
he wants me to pick
another place to be.

31:15.090 --> 31:16.962
So stay with me.

31:18.485 --> 31:20.008
In the carriage house.

31:20.052 --> 31:23.011
[Ethereal music playing]

31:23.055 --> 31:30.323
♪

31:30.366 --> 31:31.585
[Water splashing]

31:31.628 --> 31:35.632
[Gentle music playing]

31:39.723 --> 31:42.248
[Coughs]

31:46.078 --> 31:47.688
George: Hello.

31:48.863 --> 31:51.170
My name's
George Fitzsimmons, sir.

31:51.213 --> 31:53.476
What can I do for you,
Mr. Fitzsimmons?

31:53.520 --> 31:55.826
Is Madame LaVarone home?

31:55.870 --> 31:57.959
No, I'm afraid not.

31:58.003 --> 32:01.571
Ah, any idea when
she might return?

32:01.615 --> 32:02.877
When the sun goes cold.

32:02.921 --> 32:04.923
I beg your pardon?

32:04.966 --> 32:07.186
She's no longer
with us.

32:07.229 --> 32:10.363
Oh.

32:10.406 --> 32:12.017
I see.

32:12.060 --> 32:14.106
I'm not selling.

32:14.149 --> 32:16.499
Good,
and I'm not buying.

32:16.543 --> 32:18.762
I could never afford
such a lovely property.

32:18.806 --> 32:20.199
That makes two of us.

32:21.113 --> 32:23.419
What did you want
with my wife?

32:23.463 --> 32:25.682
Wife?

32:25.726 --> 32:26.945
Oh, dear.

32:26.988 --> 32:28.772
I am an idiot.

32:28.816 --> 32:30.078
My condolences.

32:30.122 --> 32:31.210
I'm -- I'm --
I'm so sorry.

32:31.253 --> 32:32.428
I had no idea
she'd remarried.

32:32.472 --> 32:33.603
Did you know her?

32:33.647 --> 32:35.562
Yes, quite a while ago.

32:35.605 --> 32:38.478
A young boy right
after the World War.

32:39.696 --> 32:43.091
See, my father was
a landscape painter.

32:43.135 --> 32:45.528
Syngin Fitzsimmons.

32:45.572 --> 32:48.923
Well, Madame LaVarone allowed
him to paint on the estate.

32:48.967 --> 32:50.142
The -- the ravine.

32:50.185 --> 32:52.883
The vineyard and cows.

32:52.927 --> 32:56.191
Oh, yeah. There's a painting
hanging in the library.

32:56.235 --> 32:59.368
Yes, it's a gift of
gratitude from my father.

32:59.412 --> 33:02.676
See, we lived in the carriage
house for three months.

33:02.719 --> 33:04.199
Still remember
the day we departed.

33:04.243 --> 33:07.159
I was desolate, sobbing.

33:07.202 --> 33:08.421
I loved being here.

33:08.464 --> 33:11.990
Well, to tell you
the truth,

33:12.033 --> 33:15.080
I did have a bit of a heart
flutter for the madame.

33:15.123 --> 33:17.299
Understandable.

33:17.343 --> 33:19.040
I'm wondering Mr...

33:19.084 --> 33:20.955
Spade.

33:20.999 --> 33:23.131
Gabrielle Spade.
Think of that.

33:23.175 --> 33:24.872
You were wondering what,
Mr. Fitzsimmons?

33:24.915 --> 33:26.178
It's...

33:26.221 --> 33:28.180
Well, I am now
an artist as well.

33:28.223 --> 33:31.009
And you want
to paint here.

33:31.052 --> 33:35.665
If my clumping around won't
be too much of a disturbance?

33:35.709 --> 33:37.232
Not at all.

33:37.276 --> 33:39.234
Come clump
whenever you want.

33:39.278 --> 33:41.454
As long as you're quiet
and I never see you.

33:41.497 --> 33:44.587
Good, consider me just
another cow in the pasture.

33:44.631 --> 33:46.285
We sold the cows

33:46.328 --> 33:49.070
right after the carriage
house burned to the ground.

33:51.333 --> 33:53.031
[Slow music playing]

33:53.074 --> 33:59.559
♪

33:59.602 --> 34:03.041
You always did have
a thing for strays.

34:03.084 --> 34:07.915
♪

34:07.958 --> 34:09.960
[Man on radio speaking French]

34:16.489 --> 34:18.665
Man on the moon.

34:21.188 --> 34:23.103
What the hell for?

34:31.591 --> 34:34.681
[Engine humming]

34:56.137 --> 34:58.444
[Slow music playing]

34:58.487 --> 35:05.233
♪

35:05.277 --> 35:11.935
♪

35:11.979 --> 35:18.681
♪

35:18.725 --> 35:21.510
[Door opens]

35:21.554 --> 35:24.687
[Footsteps approaching]

35:38.745 --> 35:40.573
Morning.

35:41.269 --> 35:43.358
Oh, Helena...

35:45.534 --> 35:48.581
...could you ask Henri
to come see me?

35:55.109 --> 35:57.416
[Insects buzzing]

36:02.986 --> 36:04.727
How do, Mr. Spade?

36:04.771 --> 36:06.207
George.

36:06.251 --> 36:09.079
What's the matter,
Jean-Pierre?

36:09.123 --> 36:12.518
You got lost
in the dark last night?

36:12.561 --> 36:16.043
Maybe you forgot you were
gonna stay off my property.

36:16.086 --> 36:18.001
Your property.
Oh, Jesus.

36:18.045 --> 36:19.742
Have you been sitting
there since last night?

36:19.786 --> 36:21.527
What are you talking about?
I wasn't here last night.

36:21.570 --> 36:22.876
Then who was?

36:22.919 --> 36:24.051
How would I know?
I wasn't here.

36:24.094 --> 36:25.226
Philippe Saint-Andre.

36:25.270 --> 36:27.097
Did you lend him
your bike?

36:27.141 --> 36:28.577
Sometimes
he just takes it.

36:28.621 --> 36:30.144
He's an old friend
after all.

36:30.188 --> 36:33.365
Oh. With friends like that,
who needs friends?

36:34.844 --> 36:36.759
Jean-Pierre.

36:36.803 --> 36:39.588
There's some things you just
don't ever want to do.

36:39.632 --> 36:41.460
[Scoffs]

36:41.503 --> 36:43.288
We have all heard
the stories.

36:43.331 --> 36:45.377
What a tough guy
you once were.

36:45.420 --> 36:46.465
There's no such thing.

36:46.508 --> 36:48.554
I wonder.

36:48.597 --> 36:50.686
Are they true stories,

36:50.730 --> 36:53.428
or just things you tell
a woman, like my wife?

36:56.388 --> 36:57.867
Hey, wait,

36:57.911 --> 37:00.827
I have a business proposition
for you, Spade.

37:02.176 --> 37:03.177
Do not laugh at me.

37:03.221 --> 37:04.831
Then don't be ridiculous.

37:04.874 --> 37:07.616
I'm very serious.
Buy my half of the health club.

37:07.660 --> 37:10.140
You mean
Marguerite's half?

37:10.184 --> 37:12.404
You talk to her
about this?

37:12.447 --> 37:14.188
She never has to know.

37:14.232 --> 37:17.235
Funny thing about drunks,
they think they make sense.

37:17.278 --> 37:20.063
You buy me out,
I disappear.

37:20.107 --> 37:23.066
You get the whole club and my
wife completely to yourself.

37:23.110 --> 37:25.330
What makes you think
that I want Marguerite,

37:25.373 --> 37:26.679
or she wants me?

37:30.030 --> 37:31.336
Think about it.

37:34.513 --> 37:36.602
You tell your old
friend Philippe,

37:36.645 --> 37:38.256
he wants to talk to me,

37:38.299 --> 37:39.779
he can come and harangue me
to my face

37:39.822 --> 37:41.563
like everyone else.

37:41.607 --> 37:44.523
[Marguerite
singing in French]

37:56.578 --> 37:58.319
Hello, Mr. Spade.

37:58.363 --> 38:00.147
Mrs. Devereux.

38:00.190 --> 38:01.496
Drink?

38:01.540 --> 38:03.237
It's a little early,
don't you think?

38:03.281 --> 38:06.980
Or a little late, depending
on one's point of view.

38:07.023 --> 38:09.025
Last night I thought
I could hear the party

38:09.069 --> 38:11.419
all the way
up at my place.
Did you now?

38:11.463 --> 38:13.203
But maybe that was just
you and Jean-Pierre

38:13.247 --> 38:15.380
throwing bottles
at each other.

38:15.423 --> 38:16.903
Did he hit you?

38:16.946 --> 38:19.384
Maybe I hit him first.

38:20.341 --> 38:22.125
I can take care
of myself.

38:22.169 --> 38:24.824
He came by this morning
on his motorcycle.

38:26.086 --> 38:28.871
For once, let's not
talk about Jean-Pierre.

38:30.395 --> 38:32.266
You should have
come in last night.

38:32.310 --> 38:35.400
Full house,
standing ovations.

38:41.231 --> 38:43.364
You sure
this is right?

38:43.408 --> 38:46.585
Like I said,
we had a full house.

38:46.628 --> 38:49.588
Your husband already thinks
I stole the joint.

38:51.067 --> 38:54.070
Jean-Pierre thinks you
stole more than the club.

38:54.114 --> 38:55.463
If he only knew.

38:55.507 --> 38:58.814
But the club is not his.
The club is mine.

38:58.858 --> 39:00.860
Ours.

39:00.903 --> 39:03.253
Is this what
set him off?

39:03.297 --> 39:04.951
Jean-Pierre
doesn't need much.

39:11.305 --> 39:14.134
[Coughing]You feeling all right?

39:14.177 --> 39:16.789
I'm fine.
Never better.

39:16.832 --> 39:19.661
The other night,
I'm walking by the cemetery

39:19.705 --> 39:22.272
and I see you inside.

39:22.316 --> 39:25.363
Evening's a nice time
to do that.

39:25.406 --> 39:28.148
Must be, as you are
there every night.

39:28.191 --> 39:30.933
Oh, you go by the
cemetery that often?

39:30.977 --> 39:32.587
I'm shopping for a plot.

39:35.677 --> 39:37.462
Two years
have passed, Sam.

39:39.028 --> 39:41.379
I stopped looking at
calendars and mirrors

39:41.422 --> 39:42.902
a long time ago.

39:44.599 --> 39:47.254
[Bells tolling]

39:47.297 --> 39:50.649
[Indistinct conversations]

40:02.878 --> 40:05.794
[Converse in French]

40:15.848 --> 40:17.458
Patrice.

40:33.039 --> 40:34.344
I'm watching my weight.

40:34.388 --> 40:36.085
Watching it do what?

40:36.956 --> 40:40.263
You might want to put
a pin on Mr. Jean-Pierre

40:40.307 --> 40:41.874
and Madame
Marguerite Devereux.

40:43.484 --> 40:44.964
They had another
battle royal last night.

40:45.007 --> 40:46.661
I know, I talked to her.

40:46.705 --> 40:48.054
Sometimes I wish
they'd just kill each other

40:48.097 --> 40:50.143
and give the rest of us
some peace.

40:50.186 --> 40:53.102
Jean-Pierre hasn't been right
since he was discharged.

40:53.146 --> 40:54.626
The war has come home.

40:54.669 --> 40:56.715
Sooner or later,
they always do.

40:56.758 --> 40:59.761
This one, this Algerian
fiasco, is different.

40:59.805 --> 41:03.722
But Jean-Pierre is a model
citizen compared to others.

41:03.765 --> 41:06.289
I don't suppose
you've heard the good news.

41:06.333 --> 41:07.813
We're getting
a bowling alley?

41:07.856 --> 41:11.904
Philippe Saint-Andre has
apparently returned home.

41:14.080 --> 41:17.083
Do I have to worry
about you and Philippe?

41:17.126 --> 41:20.086
[Man speaks French]

41:23.742 --> 41:26.745
[Coins jingling]

41:35.797 --> 41:37.756
If you don't watch out,
Patrice,

41:37.799 --> 41:39.366
you're gonna burn in hell.

41:39.409 --> 41:40.585
I'm a goalist.

41:40.628 --> 41:42.935
So to many,
I'm already there.

41:42.978 --> 41:45.807
Answer my question.What's to worry about?

41:45.851 --> 41:47.940
We've discussed two different
men who want you dead,

41:47.983 --> 41:49.637
and my breakfast
hasn't yet arrived.

41:49.681 --> 41:52.379
Yeah, but only one of
those men is a sociopath.

41:52.422 --> 41:54.816
One is enough.

41:54.860 --> 41:56.209
I told you back then

41:56.252 --> 41:57.776
that your solution
was no solution.

41:57.819 --> 42:00.779
Yeah, but you weren't
paying me.

42:02.563 --> 42:04.304
Gabrielle was.

42:06.436 --> 42:09.744
[Man on radio speaking French]

42:17.317 --> 42:20.276
[Changing radio stations]

42:20.320 --> 42:23.715
["Qu'il Fait Bon de Vivre Ici"
by Paul Bonneau, Pierre Duclos,
Eliane Blache playing]

42:23.758 --> 42:26.718
[Motorcycle engine humming]

42:26.761 --> 42:35.291
♪

42:35.335 --> 42:36.858
[Tires screeching]

42:36.902 --> 42:46.215
♪

42:46.259 --> 42:48.827
[Slow music playing]

42:48.870 --> 42:57.009
♪

42:57.052 --> 42:59.489
[Speaking French]

43:01.100 --> 43:07.323
♪

43:07.367 --> 43:09.021
Ah.

43:12.590 --> 43:14.200
Hello, Henri.

43:16.071 --> 43:19.597
Military life
treating you all right?

43:19.640 --> 43:22.077
Well, the training
is difficult

43:22.121 --> 43:24.776
mentally, physically.

43:24.819 --> 43:28.388
But what's hardest
is discipline.

43:28.431 --> 43:30.303
I do not take
orders easily.

43:30.346 --> 43:31.957
I know what you mean.

43:32.000 --> 43:33.393
You were in the army,
Mr. Spade?

43:33.436 --> 43:37.005
No, I was
a conscientious objector.

43:37.049 --> 43:40.052
You don't believe in
killing your fellow man?

43:40.095 --> 43:42.402
Oh, I think there's plenty
of men worth killing,

43:42.445 --> 43:44.839
as well as plenty of wars
worth fighting.

43:44.883 --> 43:46.885
I'd just
rather choose myself.

43:49.496 --> 43:52.368
Like the bad penny
he is,

43:52.412 --> 43:55.633
Philippe Saint-Andre
has snuck back into town.

43:55.676 --> 43:57.635
How can I help?

43:57.678 --> 43:59.027
You still spending time

43:59.071 --> 44:00.681
with that little
redheaded number?

44:00.725 --> 44:03.423
Uh...
which would that be?

44:03.466 --> 44:05.947
Redheads are all
I spend my time with.

44:05.991 --> 44:07.906
I'm talking about the
redhead you brought to dinner,

44:07.949 --> 44:10.038
the one who works
as the General's secretary.

44:10.082 --> 44:13.433
I need you to eyeball
Philippe's service file,

44:13.476 --> 44:16.958
his activities in Algeria
and everything since.

44:17.002 --> 44:19.569
I don't want you
or the redhead

44:19.613 --> 44:21.484
to get in to any trouble
over this.

44:21.528 --> 44:24.139
Your grandmother
would kill me.

44:24.183 --> 44:27.665
Well, she always said that
Saint-Andre was a bully,

44:27.708 --> 44:30.232
that he likes
to hurt people.

44:30.276 --> 44:32.104
His special gift.

44:32.147 --> 44:35.194
And that he was
blackmailing your wife

44:35.237 --> 44:38.066
before she was
your wife.

44:38.110 --> 44:42.331
Gabrielle had some difficulties
with Philippe, yes.

44:42.375 --> 44:45.117
So you sent him away?

44:45.160 --> 44:47.293
Well, I convinced him
he might live longer

44:47.336 --> 44:48.947
by going off to war.

44:51.384 --> 44:52.951
I'll see
what I can find.

44:54.735 --> 44:57.956
[Utensils clinking]

45:00.872 --> 45:04.136
[Telephone ringing]

45:14.450 --> 45:17.802
Philippe: Stay away
from Teresa.

45:17.845 --> 45:20.456
Well, if it isn't
father of the year.

45:20.500 --> 45:22.937
I mean
what I say, Spade.

45:22.981 --> 45:25.984
She doesn't want you
going near her.

45:26.027 --> 45:28.638
I hear your mother's
taken up knitting.

45:28.682 --> 45:31.990
If only you knew half as much
as you thought.

45:32.033 --> 45:34.296
I'd invite you over here
for a drink to explain it all,

45:34.340 --> 45:37.517
but I'm guessing you're up
to your neck in shit.

45:37.560 --> 45:40.259
Mind your
own fucking business.

45:43.958 --> 45:45.264
[Faint groaning]

45:45.307 --> 45:46.831
[Gun firing]

45:48.702 --> 45:50.486
Philippe?

45:50.530 --> 45:52.097
Patrice:
I told you yesterday

45:52.140 --> 45:53.663
that Philippe
had returned.

45:53.707 --> 45:55.840
I asked you
if I had to worry.

45:55.883 --> 45:57.624
And now
I'm telling you, yes.

45:57.667 --> 46:00.105
No, you are telling me

46:00.148 --> 46:04.065
that you received a phone call
from Philippe Saint-Andre,

46:04.109 --> 46:06.067
which is I admit,
concerning,

46:06.111 --> 46:07.895
but not overly so.

46:07.939 --> 46:09.941
And then you say
that during this call,

46:09.984 --> 46:13.901
you heard a gunshot,
fired by whom?

46:13.945 --> 46:15.555
Fired at him?

46:15.598 --> 46:17.122
I am saying that
Philippe was in a room

46:17.165 --> 46:18.427
where a gun was fired,

46:18.471 --> 46:20.342
either by him or at him.

46:20.386 --> 46:21.735
And I would assume
that you,

46:21.779 --> 46:23.519
legendary bloodhound
that you are,

46:23.563 --> 46:25.434
would've already
leapt out of your chair

46:25.478 --> 46:29.047
and be sniffing the
countryside in search of him.

46:29.090 --> 46:31.353
Your cheap canine
comparison aside,

46:31.397 --> 46:34.661
I do consider myself
expert on all things

46:34.704 --> 46:36.402
Philippe Saint-Andre.

46:36.445 --> 46:39.187
And I am telling you that
the man will not be found

46:39.231 --> 46:41.624
unless he wants
to be found.

46:41.668 --> 46:44.018
So what you're an expert at
is waiting.

46:44.062 --> 46:45.977
Oh, so now you insult
my professionalism?

46:46.020 --> 46:47.717
Maybe just your courage.

46:47.761 --> 46:49.545
My courage has
never been in doubt.

46:49.589 --> 46:51.896
I've got the wounds
to prove that.

46:51.939 --> 46:53.158
Unlike some of us.

46:53.201 --> 46:55.116
And now you insult
my war record?

46:55.160 --> 46:57.423
One has to have
first fought in a war

46:57.466 --> 46:59.033
to have a war record.

46:59.077 --> 47:00.948
I thought we promised to
only have this conversation

47:00.992 --> 47:01.993
when we're drunk.

47:02.036 --> 47:04.256
I'm hungover.

47:04.299 --> 47:05.910
Does that count?

47:05.953 --> 47:07.607
Tell me, Patrice,

47:07.650 --> 47:09.739
how would you feel if
Philippe hurt someone?

47:09.783 --> 47:12.003
Depends on the someone.

47:16.485 --> 47:20.272
Okay, I will put my
best man on the search.

47:20.315 --> 47:23.536
Your best man? Does that mean
your idiot brother?

47:23.579 --> 47:25.581
Is nothing good enough?

47:25.625 --> 47:27.322
Maurice is
an excellent detective.

47:27.366 --> 47:31.761
Maurice couldn't find water
if he fell out of a boat.

47:31.805 --> 47:33.372
Don't make me say it.

47:33.415 --> 47:36.288
What? That we've been through
so much together?

47:36.331 --> 47:37.898
That you owe me.

47:37.942 --> 47:39.769
You got that backwards,
haven't you?

47:39.813 --> 47:42.555
You live here
at my pleasure.

47:46.341 --> 47:48.953
[Glass shatters]

47:54.610 --> 47:56.830
Maurice.
[Snaps fingers]

48:07.580 --> 48:09.495
[Sam coughing]

48:51.102 --> 48:52.712
No?

49:10.948 --> 49:14.212
[Crickets chirping]

49:23.525 --> 49:25.745
[Slow music playing]

49:28.791 --> 49:31.620
[Coughing]

49:31.664 --> 49:37.191
♪

49:37.235 --> 49:42.762
♪

49:42.805 --> 49:44.807
[Indistinct conversations]

49:44.851 --> 49:51.989
♪

49:52.032 --> 49:59.257
♪

49:59.300 --> 50:03.043
Gabrielle: Sam,
Philippe Saint-Andre.

50:06.177 --> 50:07.743
That him?

50:10.007 --> 50:10.964
Not tonight.

50:11.008 --> 50:18.232
♪

50:18.276 --> 50:20.278
[Coughing]

50:20.321 --> 50:27.981
♪

50:28.025 --> 50:35.641
♪

50:35.684 --> 50:43.301
♪

50:46.826 --> 50:48.654
I guess
I missed the show.

50:51.657 --> 50:53.659
That better be the '52.

50:55.008 --> 50:57.315
Sometimes
Patrice is right.

50:57.358 --> 50:59.317
I mean, there's a lot
of rocks to look under

50:59.360 --> 51:01.449
between here and Algiers.

51:01.493 --> 51:03.234
And you are not
a little bit curious

51:03.277 --> 51:04.800
why Philippe
has come back?

51:04.844 --> 51:06.411
Nope.

51:06.454 --> 51:09.153
Or why he called you in
the middle of a gunfight?

51:09.196 --> 51:11.285
It was more like the
beginning of a gunfight.

51:11.329 --> 51:13.853
Even given what he tried
to do to Gabrielle.

51:13.896 --> 51:15.811
This is still
not your business?

51:15.855 --> 51:17.552
Au contraire.

51:18.205 --> 51:20.207
Hearing that
gunshot reminded me

51:20.251 --> 51:22.644
I'm allergic to other
people's business.

51:23.906 --> 51:25.473
Since when?

51:25.517 --> 51:27.867
Since moving
to beautiful Bazuel.

51:27.910 --> 51:29.390
But before you came,

51:29.434 --> 51:33.002
your talent was other
people's business, yes?

51:33.046 --> 51:35.483
"Talent."
That's rich.

51:35.527 --> 51:38.095
Paid metal as Miles
used to call it.

51:38.138 --> 51:44.101
♪

51:44.144 --> 51:45.667
People come to you
with their problems,

51:45.711 --> 51:49.062
and you end up
inheriting those problems.

51:49.106 --> 51:52.761
But you're good at fixing them,
so the problems keep coming,

51:52.805 --> 51:54.111
along with the money.

51:55.590 --> 51:56.896
In a very short while,

51:56.939 --> 51:59.203
the problems go
from small to deadly.

51:59.246 --> 52:01.030
Turns out you're
good at those, too.

52:01.074 --> 52:03.381
Maybe too good.

52:03.424 --> 52:05.209
One day you wake up,
you look in the mirror

52:05.252 --> 52:07.167
and you see someone
you don't much like.

52:07.211 --> 52:08.734
No big deal.

52:08.777 --> 52:10.910
Just don't look in
the mirror anymore.

52:12.564 --> 52:15.175
The money and the drink
are a nice distraction

52:15.219 --> 52:19.048
until you finally rot from
the inside all the way out.

52:19.092 --> 52:20.398
And no matter
how much you drink

52:20.441 --> 52:22.617
or how much money
you make,

52:22.661 --> 52:25.490
you can never get away
from your own stink.

52:27.796 --> 52:30.234
That's very vivid.

52:30.277 --> 52:33.976
But not the reason
why you are here.

52:34.020 --> 52:36.979
People don't just come
to beautiful Bazuel.

52:37.023 --> 52:39.895
You'd make a good detective,
better than me.

52:39.939 --> 52:42.942
Please, I own a bar.
Co-own.

52:44.726 --> 52:47.120
The first time I came
in this place,

52:47.164 --> 52:50.428
you were the only one who
didn't look at me cross-eyed.

52:50.471 --> 52:52.865
But I have
many times since.

53:02.309 --> 53:04.572
What are you
doing here, Spade?

53:05.660 --> 53:08.272
Making sweet love
to your wife.

53:10.056 --> 53:11.449
Now I'm going.

53:16.671 --> 53:20.197
You should be more afraid
of me.

53:20.240 --> 53:21.937
You don't know
who the fuck I am,

53:21.981 --> 53:23.896
which means
you don't know

53:23.939 --> 53:26.203
what I've done
or what I can do.

53:26.246 --> 53:27.943
You think I'm a fool?

53:27.987 --> 53:30.337
I don't think
you're a fool.

53:30.381 --> 53:32.034
I think you're like
one of those guys

53:32.078 --> 53:33.514
late at night in the bar

53:33.558 --> 53:35.386
who plays the same sad song
over and over again

53:35.429 --> 53:37.126
on the jukebox.

53:37.170 --> 53:39.825
[Both grunting]

53:41.000 --> 53:44.221
[Grunting]

53:50.662 --> 53:54.056
I remember the not-drunk
version of you.

53:54.100 --> 53:55.841
It wasn't such a bad egg.

53:56.842 --> 53:59.714
I mean, after all...

53:59.758 --> 54:01.499
she married you.

54:02.543 --> 54:05.329
[Coughing]

54:26.872 --> 54:28.743
[Slow music playing]

54:28.787 --> 54:36.229
♪

54:36.273 --> 54:43.715
♪

54:43.758 --> 54:51.200
♪

54:51.244 --> 54:53.855
Teresa: [Panting]
Mr. Spade.

54:53.899 --> 54:55.553
Teresa?

54:57.076 --> 54:58.860
Help me.

54:58.904 --> 55:01.559
[Panting]

55:01.602 --> 55:08.261
♪

55:19.968 --> 55:22.144
I ran the whole way.Tell me what happened

55:22.188 --> 55:24.103
and start with whose blood
you're wearing.

55:25.322 --> 55:26.497
My father's.

55:26.540 --> 55:28.455
Philippe
came to see you?

55:28.499 --> 55:29.587
Someone shot him.

55:29.630 --> 55:31.023
Did you see who?

55:31.066 --> 55:32.372
It was before.

55:32.416 --> 55:34.853
Did he tell you
who shot him?

55:34.896 --> 55:37.072
He said,
"Very bad men."

55:37.116 --> 55:39.510
As in men
worse than him?

55:39.553 --> 55:41.903
I know people
don't like my father,

55:41.947 --> 55:42.948
but they don't know him.

55:42.991 --> 55:44.732
Not the way I do.

55:44.776 --> 55:46.343
Still, we're sitting here
because your father got shot

55:46.386 --> 55:48.780
by, and I quote,
"some very bad men,"

55:48.823 --> 55:51.783
which I can only assume was
over some very bad business.

55:51.826 --> 55:53.393
And yet
despite the danger,

55:53.437 --> 55:55.787
he somehow figures that
the best person to run to

55:55.830 --> 55:57.310
is his 14-year-old
daughter.

55:57.354 --> 56:00.531
I'm 15.
[Speaks French]

56:00.574 --> 56:02.794
So I'm told.
Where is he now?

56:04.273 --> 56:06.537
Teresa,
where is Philippe?

56:06.580 --> 56:08.800
-Can I have another?
-No.

56:08.843 --> 56:10.976
So he knocks on the door
with a bullet in him,

56:11.019 --> 56:13.152
gives you a hug,
and then what, just leaves?

56:13.195 --> 56:16.764
Yes.And during that brief stay,
he did what?

56:16.808 --> 56:18.636
Said what?

56:18.679 --> 56:20.942
Stop thinking about what lie
he wants you to tell

56:20.986 --> 56:23.118
and tell me what
actually happened.

56:24.555 --> 56:26.774
The people who shot him,

56:26.818 --> 56:28.385
they followed him
to the convent?

56:28.428 --> 56:30.299
I don't know
who shot Papa.

56:30.343 --> 56:32.171
Maybe the monk.

56:32.214 --> 56:33.912
He came right after
Papa left.

56:33.955 --> 56:35.783
He started banging on
the gate with a stick.

56:35.827 --> 56:37.742
He wanted to see
the Mother Superior.

56:37.785 --> 56:39.526
This monk,
what did he look like?

56:39.570 --> 56:42.268
Ugly face with a --
with a raspy voice.

56:42.311 --> 56:44.662
Big nose, brown eyes?
One of those floppy hoods?

56:44.705 --> 56:46.315
-You know him?
-I've seen him.

56:46.359 --> 56:47.969
What did he want
with the Mother Superior?

56:48.013 --> 56:49.406
I don't know.

56:49.449 --> 56:52.060
He barged in and he
started shouting at her.

56:52.104 --> 56:53.540
She told him to get out,

56:53.584 --> 56:56.195
but he took the Lord's
name in vain and then,

56:56.238 --> 56:58.023
and then he hit her.

56:58.066 --> 56:59.894
Is she all right?

56:59.938 --> 57:01.287
I don't know.

57:01.330 --> 57:02.810
Everything was
so confused after that.

57:02.854 --> 57:04.421
Everyone hid.
Not everyone.

57:04.464 --> 57:06.205
You came here, why?

57:06.248 --> 57:07.989
'Cause I'm the oldest
and the fastest.

57:08.033 --> 57:10.688
Yeah, but why come here
and not the Gendarmerie?

57:16.389 --> 57:18.043
He frightens me.

57:19.871 --> 57:22.526
You stay here.
Don't move.

57:41.414 --> 57:44.199
[Dialing]

57:52.077 --> 57:54.906
[Ringing]

58:20.671 --> 58:22.847
Sorry to wake you.

58:31.029 --> 58:32.726
There's a problem.

58:40.386 --> 58:42.344
Helena will be here
in a minute.

58:42.388 --> 58:44.608
I'm gonna go check
things out.

58:55.923 --> 58:59.971
If trouble comes,
read the book.

59:04.062 --> 59:05.498
[Door closes]

59:12.766 --> 59:14.594
[Slow music playing]

59:14.638 --> 59:22.863
♪

